      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIDNIGHT ALIBI (1) is a progressive mare who brings strong form from Victoria. Recorded back to-back Bendigo wins from wider draws than this then chased along the sprint lane for second at Kilmore last week. Should get every chance from the ace draw. TITIWHA (7) has been racing well and could be close to a win having come from a similar draw for second at his latest appearance at this circuit and distance, beaten less than 4 metres. With even luck he could take care of this line-up. JANIE BLU (8) draws much wider than in her last-start win by 2.5 metres here five weeks ago but she was kept up to the mark with a trial win since. CATIES SON (4) must be considered after back-to-back Victorian placings, the latest a third from this barrier at Kilmore.",
